# **Security Assessments**

Tevico enables users to capture the security posture of their AWS infrastructure by running Security Assessments. There are two types of assessments supported by Tevico. 

**1\. Standard Security Assessment**

Tevico provides a consolidated Security Assessment report which gives an aggregated view of the findings by resource type, status, and severity. You can assess your AWS account security levels using the security score based on CIS AWS Foundations Benchmark v1.2.0 and AWS Foundational Security Best Practices v1.0.0. You will get actionable recommendations for security remediation. 

**2\. Advanced Security Assessment**  
   
The Advanced Security Assessment generates the report across various security standards such as CIS-1.2, CIS-1.4, PCI-DSS, NIST, GDPR, SOC2 & 15, HIPAA, and other standards along with guidance for security posture enhancements.  
Detailed risk analysis of the generated findings at individual service and resource levels is provided in the summary report for a better infrastructure remediation approach.

## **Enable Standard Security Assessment** 

1. Login to [https://console.tevi.co](https://console.tevi.co)  
2. Click **Dashboard** on the navigation bar on the left. On the right side of the page, there are four tabs each for Cost, Security, Reliability & Inventory.

![Enable Standard Security Assessment](images/Security%20Assessments/Enable%20Standard%20Security%20Assessment/2.1.png)

3. Click **Security.**

![Enable Standard Security Assessment](images/Security%20Assessments/Enable%20Standard%20Security%20Assessment/3.1.png)

4. In the **Assessments** sub-section, click **Explore Reports.**

![Enable Standard Security Assessment](images/Security%20Assessments/Enable%20Standard%20Security%20Assessment/4.1.png)

5. Click **Generate** under Standard Security Assessment.

![Enable Standard Security Assessment](images/Security%20Assessments/Enable%20Standard%20Security%20Assessment/5.1.png)

6. Select the **Region** from the drop-down list to run the Standard Security Assessment based on where the existing workload is. You can select one region at a time for a single Standard Security Assessment.

![Enable Standard Security Assessment](images/Security%20Assessments/Enable%20Standard%20Security%20Assessment/6.1.png)

![Enable Standard Security Assessment](images/Security%20Assessments/Enable%20Standard%20Security%20Assessment/6.2.jpg)

7. When the user clicks on **Open AWS Config**, they will receive details about the AWS pricing for the Config service and guidance on setting up a budget for it. Users can either set up a budget by selecting **Set Budget Now** or proceed without setting up any budget.

![Enable Standard Security Assessment](images/Security%20Assessments/Enable%20Standard%20Security%20Assessment/7.1.jpg)

8. Open a new tab and navigate to the AWS Management Console's Setup AWS Config page. Keep the default settings unchanged and click **Next** to proceed to **Step 2: Rules** page.

![Enable Standard Security Assessment](images/Security%20Assessments/Enable%20Standard%20Security%20Assessment/8.1.png)

![Enable Standard Security Assessment](images/Security%20Assessments/Enable%20Standard%20Security%20Assessment/8.2.png)

9. There is no need to select any specific rule before clicking **Next**. The user will then be taken to **Step 3: Review.**

![Enable Standard Security Assessment](images/Security%20Assessments/Enable%20Standard%20Security%20Assessment/9.1.png)

![Enable Standard Security Assessment](images/Security%20Assessments/Enable%20Standard%20Security%20Assessment/9.2.png)

10. Click **Confirm** to enable AWS Config. The **AWS Config Enabled** status will now be visible on Tevico as well.

![Enable Standard Security Assessment](images/Security%20Assessments/Enable%20Standard%20Security%20Assessment/10.1.png)

![Enable Standard Security Assessment](images/Security%20Assessments/Enable%20Standard%20Security%20Assessment/10.2.jpg)

11. Click **Generate Report**. Tevico will initiate the assessment in your account. This assessment typically takes around 5-6 hours to complete, after which the data will begin to appear on the dashboard.

![Enable Standard Security Assessment](images/Security%20Assessments/Enable%20Standard%20Security%20Assessment/11.1.jpg)

![Enable Standard Security Assessment](images/Security%20Assessments/Enable%20Standard%20Security%20Assessment/11.2.jpg)

![Enable Standard Security Assessment](images/Security%20Assessments/Enable%20Standard%20Security%20Assessment/11.3.jpg)

![Enable Standard Security Assessment](images/Security%20Assessments/Enable%20Standard%20Security%20Assessment/11.4.jpg)

![Enable Standard Security Assessment](images/Security%20Assessments/Enable%20Standard%20Security%20Assessment/11.5.jpg)

## **Enable Advanced Security Assessment** 

1. Login to [https://console.tevi.co](https://console.tevi.co)

2. Click **Dashboard** on the navigation bar on the left. On the right side of the page, there are four tabs each for Cost, Security, Reliability & Inventory.  
   

![Enable Advanced Security Assessment](images/Security%20Assessments/Enable%20Advanced%20Security%20Assessment/2.1.png)

3. Click **Security Dashboard.**

![Enable Advanced Security Assessment](images/Security%20Assessments/Enable%20Advanced%20Security%20Assessment/3.1.png)

4. In the **Assessments** sub-section, click **Explore Reports.**  
   

![Enable Advanced Security Assessment](images/Security%20Assessments/Enable%20Advanced%20Security%20Assessment/4.1.png)

5. Click the **Generate** button in Advanced Security Assessment.

![Enable Advanced Security Assessment](images/Security%20Assessments/Enable%20Advanced%20Security%20Assessment/5.1.png)

6. Fill in the necessary fields:

   a. Select the **Region(s)** based on where the workload is.

![Enable Advanced Security Assessment](images/Security%20Assessments/Enable%20Advanced%20Security%20Assessment/6.a.1.png)

b. Select **Compliance** from the drop-down list.

![Enable Advanced Security Assessment](images/Security%20Assessments/Enable%20Advanced%20Security%20Assessment/6.b.png)

c. Select the **S3 Bucket** in which the assessment findings are to be stored.

![Enable Advanced Security Assessment](images/Security%20Assessments/Enable%20Advanced%20Security%20Assessment/6.c.png)

d. Copy the S3 bucket policy visible in Tevico. It is required to attach this policy to the S3 bucket where the assessment findings are to be stored.  
   

![Enable Advanced Security Assessment](images/Security%20Assessments/Enable%20Advanced%20Security%20Assessment/6.d.png)

**Note**: The S3 bucket policy is provided below for reference. Replace \<AWS-Account-ID\> and \<role-name\> with the appropriate values before attaching the policy to the S3 bucket.

e. To attach required S3 bucket policy, login to AWS Management Console and open S3. For the required S3 bucket, go to the **Permissions** tab.  
   

![Enable Advanced Security Assessment](images/Security%20Assessments/Enable%20Advanced%20Security%20Assessment/6.e.1.png)

![Enable Advanced Security Assessment](images/Security%20Assessments/Enable%20Advanced%20Security%20Assessment/6.e.2.png)

f. In the Bucket Policy section, click on the **Edit** button and paste the given bucket policy statement.

![Enable Advanced Security Assessment](images/Security%20Assessments/Enable%20Advanced%20Security%20Assessment/6.f.png)

g. After pasting the policy, click the **Save** button.

![Enable Advanced Security Assessment](images/Security%20Assessments/Enable%20Advanced%20Security%20Assessment/6.g.1.png)

![Enable Advanced Security Assessment](images/Security%20Assessments/Enable%20Advanced%20Security%20Assessment/6.g.2.png)

h. Go back to Tevico. Confirm the changes by ensuring that all status checks are passing and click **Submit.**

![Enable Advanced Security Assessment](images/Security%20Assessments/Enable%20Advanced%20Security%20Assessment/6.h.1.png)

![Enable Advanced Security Assessment](images/Security%20Assessments/Enable%20Advanced%20Security%20Assessment/6.h.2.png)

7. Click **Submit** once again to get the Advanced Security Assessment results**.** 

![Enable Advanced Security Assessment](images/Security%20Assessments/Enable%20Advanced%20Security%20Assessment/7.1.png)

8. The Advanced Security Assessment report will be ready after the scan which takes around 20-30 minutes to complete.

![Enable Advanced Security Assessment](images/Security%20Assessments/Enable%20Advanced%20Security%20Assessment/8.1.png)

![Enable Advanced Security Assessment](images/Security%20Assessments/Enable%20Advanced%20Security%20Assessment/8.2.png)

![Enable Advanced Security Assessment](images/Security%20Assessments/Enable%20Advanced%20Security%20Assessment/8.3.png)

![Enable Advanced Security Assessment](images/Security%20Assessments/Enable%20Advanced%20Security%20Assessment/8.4.png)

![Enable Advanced Security Assessment](images/Security%20Assessments/Enable%20Advanced%20Security%20Assessment/8.5.png)

### **Compliance**  

Tevico provides 21 compliance standards to help businesses meet regulatory requirements such as ISO, HIPAA, and GDPR, covering security, privacy, and regulatory needs.

You can easily generate a compliance report. The selected compliances will be listed under the compliance-based status section. To export the report, simply click on the export option and choose your preferred format—either PDF or Excel.

![Compliance](images/Security%20Assessments/Enable%20Advanced%20Security%20Assessment/compliances/1.1.png)

Users can enhance their security posture by enabling compliance standards. By simply clicking the "Enable" button, users can activate the relevant compliance standard, automatically generating findings corresponding to that specific compliance framework.

![Compliance](images/Security%20Assessments/Enable%20Advanced%20Security%20Assessment/compliances/1.2.png)

For a detailed view for specific compliance click on any mentioned compliance standard in the “Compliance column”. 

1. **PCI 3.2.1**

**Standards that are not supported by the solution.**

* **ISO27001**  
  ISO 27001 sets the framework for all organizations to establish, implement, operate, monitor, review, maintain and continually improve an ISMS (information security management system).  
* **FIPS 140-2**  
  FIPS (Federal Information Processing Standard) 140-2 is the benchmark for validating the effectiveness of cryptographic hardware.  
* **FISMA**   
  The Federal Information Security Modernization Act (FISMA) defines a framework of guidelines and security standards to protect government information and operations.  
* **ITAR**  
  ITAR rules regulate the export of defense articles and services, including technological products and services and technical data.
